@endnode

@node Installation "Installation"

  You must already have ebp V1.0 installed on your system to use this
  distribution.

  This archive contains two files:

    1. The replacement executable.

    2. This documentation

  Simply replace the files in the ebp1.0 distribution with the files in
  this distribution

@endnode

@node Usage "Usage"

  You can start the program by clicking on the icon, or from the CLI.

  Main Gadgets:

  Files
  -----

      Open a Book
      -----------

        When you click on this gadget you will be prompted for a book to open.
        The book will then be displayed in it's own scrollable resizeable
        window.  Up to ten of these windows can be opened at a time.

      Save Matches
      ------------

        This allows you to save the matched verses from the previous search.

      Load Matches
      ------------

        This is where you load matches prevoiusly saved.

  Bookmarks
  ---------

      Add Bookmark
      ------------

        Add a verse to the bookmark file.

      Remove Bookmark
      ---------------

        Erase a bookmark from the bookmark file.

      Goto Bookmark
      -------------

        Select a bookmark to open.

  Search
  ------

    Opens the search requester where you define the search parameters,
    preforms the search, and displays the first result.

  Display Matches
  ---------------

    Displays a scrollable window of all the matches for the last search.
    You can then select one to be displayed.

  Next Match
  ----------

    Moves to the next match.

  Prev. Match
  -----------

    Moves to the last match.



  Search Requester
  ----------------

     This is where you define the search parameters, there are three
     parts to this requester, they are as follows:

     1.  THE SEARCH DATA - You are required to enter a single word, a list
         of words, or a phrase to search for.  A word list should have the
         words separated by a comma (,)

         Ex: deep , water

         On the other hand, phrase should contain no commas.

         If when searching for a word, you do not wish to match bigger words
         containing a search word, simply include a space before and after the
         word in the search list.

         For example you are searching for the word "and" the search would also
         match words "sand","hand", etc. To get around that you simply specify
         the word " and ".  In the future padding your search words with spaces
         will not be necessary.

     2.  SEARCH SCOPE - You are required to specify what part of the bible
         to search.  You can either search the old testament, new testament,
         or the entire bible.  In the future, you will be able to search the
         verses matched in the previous search.

     3.  SEARCH TYPE - There are four search types you can select

           A.  AND - a match will include all words in your word list.

           B.  OR  - a match will include any word in your word list.

           C.  PHRASE - a match will have the exact phrase you entered
               (no commas allowed).

           D.  MATCHES FROM LAST SEARCH - This will only search the verses
               matched in the previous search.

  To quit, simply close the main gadget window.

@endnode

